place.name: STRINGTSON
place.gazetteerText: STRINGSTON, a parish in Williton district, Somerset; 6 miles E of Williton r. station. Post town, Holford, under Bridgewater. Acres, 1,193. Real property, £828. Pop., 144. Houses, 25. The manor belongs to Sir H. Oglander, Bart. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Kilve. The church is plain. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
